description:
The second episode in a series about the mysterious disappearance Kris Kremers and Lisanne Froon in Panama, April 2014

In this episode we cover the disappearance and the subsequent search, the biggest operation ever conducted in Panama.

For further reading on this case:
The blog of Scarlet R:  https://koudekaas.blogspot.com/
The website of Imperfect Plan: https://imperfectplan.com/
The YouTube site of Romain C:  https://www.youtube.com/user/francepatriote1/videos
The YouTube site of Scarlet R:  https://www.youtube.com/@scarletr.7753
The book 'Lost in the Jungle': https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/58580012-lost-in-the-jungle
The book 'Still lost in Panama':  https://www.amazon.com/Still-Lost-Panama-Tragedy-Pianista-ebook/dp/B0CW1HXXQ9

comments.text: If the photos happened to be taken in the dark, the flash could serve as evidence of their location when, in a panicked, fast-moving, and survival instinct, they activated the camera's burst or automatic mode in the evening because they couldn't see anything. So where were they before?
comments.author: @Christianhoude-007

comments.text:
Eileen definitely knows what REALLY happened. but didn't dare say it so she ran away from there soon after and back to Germany. Well, that's a whole bunch of gangsters.

People disappear there all the time, not just these girls, that says a lot about this place on earth.
comments.author: @larsfredblom9017
